## Heaps — High-Level Concept

Covered what a heap is, concept-only (no implementation yet — saving the full problem for later).

A heap is a container with one special power: no matter how many items you throw into it, it can always hand you the **biggest one instantly**. Throw in 50 numbers in random order, ask for the largest, and it's there immediately. Ask again, you get the next largest.

**Mental model:** a pile of resumes that automatically keeps the strongest candidate on top. You don't re-sort the whole pile every time — the structure maintains the "best on top" property for you.

This is the tool that makes certain LeetCode problems efficient: when you repeatedly need "the current max (or min)" out of a changing collection, a heap gives it to you fast instead of re-scanning everything each time.

